OL,3,CFormer leader of Reform UK in Wales to
OL,4,Cdeny alleged Russian bribery charges
OL,6,FGill allegedly made statements in the
OL,7,FEuropean Parliament and in opinion
OL,8,Fpieces to news outlets, such as 112
OL,9,FUkraine, which were "supportive of a
OL,10,Fparticular narrative" which would
OL,11,F"benefit Russia regarding events in
OL,12,FUkraine".
OL,14,FThe defendant is alleged to have been
OL,15,Ftasked by Oleg Voloshyn on at least
OL,16,Feight occasions to make specific
OL,17,Fstatements in return for money.
